cs.CV, cs.BIO, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.HC 

The paper concerns the application of deep learning methods to ultrasound imaging for understanding the content of muscle images in terms of its measured state. This falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV) as well as bioinformatics (cs.BIO). The use of deep learning methods for prediction also suggests the involvement of machine learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the focus on medical applications and the use of electromyography data suggests a potential overlap with human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
